bug.description:
Built latest version from HEAD with ffmpeg support enabled on Windows 10.
When you connect to a rtsp stream and the resource (read: the streaming server) is unavailable an indefinite hang on Windows is observed.
I've done some initial research and if you want to handle transient connection issues you need to specify a interrupt callback as per <denchmark-link:https://ffmpeg.org/doxygen/2.7/structAVFormatContext.html#a5b37acfe4024d92ee510064e80920b40>documentation</denchmark-link>
 before  is called.
Digging through their bug tracker i found a related <denchmark-link:https://trac.ffmpeg.org/ticket/2694>issue</denchmark-link>
 submitted about two years ago.
Repo:
auto vc = new cv::VideoCapture();
auto success = vc->open("rstp://192.168.1.200/media/video1");
// -- indefinite hang
